I"î<h1 id="consensus">Consensus</h1>

<p>Specification of the consensus protocol implemented in CometBFT.</p>

<h2 id="contents">Contents</h2>

<ul>
  <li><a href="./consensus-paper">Consensus Paper</a> - Latex paper on
<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1807.04938">arxiv</a> describing the
Tendermint consensus algorithm, adopted in CometBFT, with proofs of safety and termination.</li>
  <li><a href="/v0.37/spec/consensus/bft-time/">BFT Time</a> - How the timestamp in a CometBFT
block header is computed in a Byzantine Fault Tolerant manner</li>
  <li><a href="/v0.37/spec/consensus/creating-proposal/">Creating Proposal</a> - How a proposer
creates a block proposal for consensus</li>
  <li><a href="./light-client">Light Client Protocol</a> - A protocol for light weight consensus
verification and syncing to the latest state</li>
  <li><a href="/v0.37/spec/consensus/signing.md">Signing</a> - Rules for cryptographic signatures
produced by validators.</li>
  <li><a href="/v0.37/spec/consensus/wal.md">Write Ahead Log</a> - Write ahead log used by the
consensus state machine to recover from crashes.</li>
</ul>

<p>There is also a <a href="/v0.37/spec/consensus/consensus/">stale markdown description</a> of the consensus state machine
(TODO update this).</p>
